<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,310,684,710]" box="[189,310,684,710]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,684,710]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,684,710]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,730,932]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
A combination of male genitalic characters is diagnostic of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[928,1148,730,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[928,1148,730,757]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Aprionus fontanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1160,1258,731,757]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as follows (
<figureCitation box="[198,307,765,792]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[342,1218,1012,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[227,1361,1008,1936]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 14. Aprionus fontanus sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scale lines: 0.05 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838661/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). The long tegmen is sharply pointed apically (↓), undoubtedly a firm shape considering that the margins are reinforced. The apical portion of the gonostylus is strongly bent dorsally to dorsolaterally (↓); the gonostylar tooth is flattened; 2 strong bristles are inserted medially. The subrectangular ventral plate has a characteristic pattern of dark markings, including an inverted V-shape medially on the anterior edge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838661" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3838661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838661/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" startId="24.[189,232,1968,1994]" targetBox="[342,1218,1012,1932]" targetPageId="24">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1968,2030]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,282,1968,1994]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[290,507,1968,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[290,507,1968,1995]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Aprionus fontanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,609,1969,1995]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, ♂. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[777,798,1968,1994]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A</emphasis>
. Genitalia, ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1034,1054,1969,1995]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">B</emphasis>
. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scale lines: 0.05 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection box="[189,1181,267,342]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,324,267,293]" box="[189,324,267,293]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,267,293]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1181,315,342]" box="[189,1181,315,342]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[428,529,315,341]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontanus">
<emphasis box="[428,529,315,341]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">fontanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is a Latin adjective meaning ‘belonging to the spring’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
