<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,457,573,599]" box="[189,457,573,599]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,573,599]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,573,599]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,621,722]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof, 1997" authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="1997" box="[189,614,621,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angeloides">
<emphasis box="[189,430,621,648]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Aprionus angeloides</emphasis>
Jaschhof, 1997
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from Swedish Lapland, bears a faint resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[220,355,658,685]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[220,355,658,685]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A. fontanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[364,459,659,685]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in particular regarding the outline of the gonostylus and tegmen (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof M." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 552" refId="ref16637" refString="Jaschhof M. 1998. Revision der &quot; Lestremiinae &quot; (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) der Holarktis. Studia Dipterologica Supplement 4: 1 - 552." type="journal article" year="1998">Jaschhof 1998</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 148).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,403,763,789]" box="[189,403,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,403,763,789]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,403,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Other characters</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,410,811,838]" box="[189,410,811,838]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Body size 
<quantity box="[313,406,811,838]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,878,979]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
HEAD. Postfrons setose. Eye bridge 2–3 ommatidia long dorsally. A sparse row of 7 postocular bristles. Neck of fourth flagellomere slightly longer than node, translucent sensilla simply hair-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1385,916,942]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[342,1218,1012,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[227,1361,1008,1936]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 14. Aprionus fontanus sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scale lines: 0.05 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838661/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Palpus 3-segmented, apical segment longest of all.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,635,1020,1052]" box="[189,635,1020,1052]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
WING. ApicR 
<subScript attach="left" box="[343,352,1038,1052]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">1</subScript>
3.0 times as long as Rs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,909,1087,1114]" box="[189,909,1087,1114]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">LEGS. Claws subrectangular, toothless. Empodia rudimentary.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1398,1155,1218]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
TERMINALIA (
<figureCitation box="[344,457,1155,1181]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[342,1218,1012,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[227,1361,1008,1936]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 14. Aprionus fontanus sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scale lines: 0.05 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838661/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Ninth tergite subrectangular, anterior margin fully sclerotized. Gonocoxites rounded rather than pointed ventroposteriorly; dorsal bridge extends far anteriorly, subtrapezoid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
